import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby('date')['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['rate'])
    
    ax = plt.gca()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the overall trend of unemployment rate across all industries?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    industry_rate = data.groupby('series')['rate'].mean()
    industry_rate = industry_rate.sort_values(ascending=False)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = industry_rate.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("Which industry has the highest and lowest unemployment rate?")
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    pivot_data = data.pivot_table(index='year', columns='month', values='rate', aggfunc='mean')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.gca()
    heatmap = ax.imshow(pivot_data, cmap='coolwarm', aspect='auto')
    plt.colorbar(heatmap, label='Unemployment Rate')
    
    ax.set_xticks(range(len(pivot_data.columns)))
    ax.set_yticks(range(len(pivot_data.index)))
    ax.set_xticklabels(pivot_data.columns)
    ax.set_yticklabels(pivot_data.index)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xlabel('Month')
    plt.ylabel('Year')
    plt.title('How does the unemployment rate vary by month and year?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
